quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  5,18,"Moreover, the Jews and the Christians said, “We are the children of Allah and are His beloved.” Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Why then does He punish you for your misdeeds?” Rather, you are but human beings from among those He created. He forgives whom He wills, and He punishes whom He wills, for to Allah belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth and what lies between them, and to Him is the destiny."
  5,19,"O People of the Scripture, Our Messenger has surely come to you, making things clear to you—after a cessation of sending messengers—so that you cannot say, “Neither a herald of glad tidings nor a warner has come to us.” In fact, a herald of glad tidings and a warner has come to you, for Allah is All-Powerful over everything."
  5,20,"And recall when Moses said to his people, “O my people, remember Allah’s blessing upon you when He made among you prophets and made you kings and brought you what He never brought anyone<i class=""s"">(else) </i>in all communities.”"
  5,21,"“O my people, enter the Holy Land which Allah has prescribed for you, and do not turn on your heels lest you return as losers.”"
  5,22,"They said, “O Moses, there are certainly tyrannical people in it, and we will certainly not enter it until they depart it. So if they depart it, we will then surely enter.”"
  5,23,"Two men of those who fear<i class=""s"">(God) </i>—on whom Allah had bestowed His blessings—said, “Enter upon them by the gate, for as soon as you have entered it, you are then indeed overcomers. And place your trust in Allah if you are believers.”"
